The paper deals with the interpretability and explainability of CNNs for image classification, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of gradient-based backpropagation, which is a common technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method in terms of accuracy and discrimination, which are key concerns in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of the decision process of CNNs, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
